LOCATION:Newman Auditorium (Emeritus Hall) - Santa Rosa Campus
SUMMARY:Bennett Friedman Quartet
DESCRIPTION:The Music Department of Santa Rosa Junior College presents a 
 jazz concert by the Bennett Friedman Quartet on Thursday\, April 2\, at 7
 :30 PM in Newman Auditorium on the SRJC campus. Guitarist Randy Vincent\,
  bassist Jeff Denson\, and drummer Kendrick Freeman will be featured.  Th
 e quartet will perform "Take Five" by Paul Desmond\, compositions of Bobb
 y Hutcherson\, Wayne Shorter\, and others.  General admission is $15\, an
 d $10 for students and seniors. Parking on campus is $4. Proceeds from th
 e concert benefit the SRJC Foundation Jazz Studies Fund.Visit SRJC's Musi
 c Department website here! (https://music.santarosa.edu/events)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Music Department of Santa Rosa Juni
 or College presents a jazz concert by the Bennett Friedman Quartet on Thu
 rsday\, April 2\, at 7:30 PM in Newman Auditorium on the SRJC campus. Gui
 tarist Randy Vincent\, bassist Jeff Denson\, and drummer Kendrick Freeman
  will be featured.<br /><br />  The quartet will perform "Take Five" by P
 aul Desmond\, compositions of Bobby Hutcherson\, Wayne Shorter\, and othe
 rs.<br /><br />  General admission is $15\, and $10 for students and seni
 ors. Parking on campus is $4. Proceeds from the concert benefit the SRJC 
 Foundation Jazz Studies Fund.</p><p><a href="https://music.santarosa.edu/
 events" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit SRJC's Music Department webs
 ite here!</a></p>
